Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Fragrant King Prawn and Veg Noodle Stir-Fry in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} into thirds.

Cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

== Noodles ==

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nests{125%g} and broccoli to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

== Stir-Fry ==

While the noodles cook, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and pepper. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain the @king prawns{150%g}. Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns.

Stir the prawns and @ginger, garlic & lemongrass puree{15%g} into the pan and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @bulgogi sauce{100%g}, and @water{50%ml} to the pan.

> See pantry for amount of water - about 50 ml needed.

Stir to combine and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles and a good squeeze of lime juice from a lime wedge to the pan. Toss to coat in the sauce, ~{1%minute}.

> The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

== To Serve ==

When ready, share your prawn and veg stir-fry between your serving bowls.

Scatter over the @cashew nuts{40%g} and serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!